What it Does
It greets and takes a customer's order for Zach's coffee shop

What it Demonstrates
The practicality of variables 

Potential Improvements
We could add input validation for invalid menu items


  Script
print("Hello, welcome to Zach's coffee shop!")

CustomerName = input("What is your name?\n" )
Menu = "\nBlack Coffee S/M/L/XL\nMacchiato S/M/L\nLondon Fog S/M/L\n"
print("\nHello " + CustomerName + ", thank you so much for coming in today! Here is our menu.\n" + Menu)\

CustomerOrder = input("What can I get started for you " + CustomerName +"?\n")

print("\nYou got it " + CustomerName + ". I will have your " + CustomerOrder + " right out in a few minutes!" )

